newsitem.title: EGYPT: Egyptian pound interbank overnight rates rise.
newsitem.headline: Egyptian pound interbank overnight rates rise.

text.p: Overnight interbank rates on the Egyptian pound rose in the private sector on Monday to between 10-1/8 and 10-3/8 percent from Sunday's range of 10 and 10-1/4 percent, bankers said.
"There was unusually large demand, particularly before a 600 million pound issue of 90-day T-bills on Wednesday," said one.
One-week rates went up to between 10-1/4 and 10-5/16 percent from 10-1/4 percent, the bankers added.
State-owned banks kept their minimum interbank lending rate at 10-1/2 percent, they said.
